[Viet Nam has submitted its follow-up reports no. 9 and 10 on 19 and 20 Mar 2019, respectively. Links to all reports and a summarising interactive map are available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=29617.

As of 20 Mar 2019, the event in Viet Nam, which reportedly started 1 Feb 2019, was summarised by the OIE as follows:

Total outbreaks = 208 (submitted)
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Swine / 11 501 / 1324 / 465 / 11 036 / 0

No cases in wild boar have been reported from Viet Nam.

The wide distribution of the ASF virus in China is also reflected by the detection of the virus in food parcels/consignments found or confiscated in airports beyond China's mainland, particularly in Taiwan. The most recent report was published on Thu 21 Mar 2019 (http://focustaiwan.tw/news/asoc/201903210019.aspx), related to fish balls containing pork that were tested for ASF on 13 Mar 2019, after being found discarded at Kaohsiung International Airport. The product is believed to have been brought into Taiwan by a passenger who disembarked from a Uni Air flight from Fuzhou. This case brings the total number of pork products, confirmed as infected with ASF upon arrival in Taiwan to 34 since October 2018 (one in October, 2 in November, and 4 in December 2018, 11 in January, 11 in February, and 5 in March 2019, according to statistics compiled by Taiwan's Central Emergency Operation Center for ASF. - Mod.AS

